		<td><b>Re: testing list</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><ul><li>The BBCode element for ordered and unordered lists is called &quot;list&quot;</li><li>The list element is transformed into an HTML ol or ul element based on its attribute being present or absent</li><li>Each item in the list is inside a &quot;*&quot; element</li><li>Like HTML (and unlike XHTML), BBCode has elements whose closing tag is optional in certain circumstances because the element can't directly contain itself</li><li>For example, the closing tag for the * element is optional</li><li>To see the BBCode source for this post, click the quote button</li></ul>

		

		</td>
